4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a person commits the crime
6 of unlawful possession with intent to distribute a
7 controlled substance if he or she knowingly possesses
8 more than two grams, but less than four grams, of any
9 mixture containing Fentanyl, any synthetic controlled
10 substance Fentanyl, or any synthetic controlled
11 substance Fentanyl analogue.
12 This bill would provide that a person commits
13 the crime of unlawful possession with intent to
14 distribute a controlled substance if he or she
15 knowingly possesses more than one-half gram, but less
16 than one gram, or more than two grams, but less than
17 four grams, of certain mixtures of Fentanyl or Fentanyl
18 analogues.
19 Under existing law, a person commits the crime
20 of trafficking in illegal drugs if he or she is
21 knowingly in actual or constructive possession of one
22 gram or more of Fentanyl or any synthetic controlled
23 substance Fentanyl analogue as a single component.
24 This bill would also provide that a person
25 commits the crime of trafficking in illegal drugs if he
26 or she is knowingly in actual or constructive
27 possession of certain mixtures of Fentanyl or Fentanyl
28 analogues.
Page 1

analogues.
SB309 INTRODUCED
